00:26:47.990 --> 00:26:50.240
he must not be doing well out there

00:26:50.610 --> 00:26:52.410
and was too ashamed to come back.

00:26:53.440 --> 00:26:54.440
What do you think?

00:26:55.010 --> 00:26:58.080
Grandma, you don't need
to make excuses for him.

00:26:58.330 --> 00:26:59.410
I don't hate him.

00:26:59.830 --> 00:27:02.240
He must be doing well,
that's why he doesn't come back.

00:27:02.240 --> 00:27:05.100
It's a good thing if he can
have a good life out there.

00:27:06.720 --> 00:27:08.070
My grandson is right.

00:27:08.810 --> 00:27:10.540
My grandson has such ambition.

00:27:12.590 --> 00:27:13.790
In my life,

00:27:14.680 --> 00:27:16.030
I got a good grandson.

00:27:18.880 --> 00:27:19.830
I guess

00:27:22.430 --> 00:27:24.590
if he's really

00:27:24.620 --> 00:27:26.310
doing well out there,

00:27:27.900 --> 00:27:29.180
I could

00:27:31.700 --> 00:27:33.350
die in peace.

00:27:34.880 --> 00:27:36.940
What are you talking about, Grandma?

00:27:37.780 --> 00:27:38.780
With your health,

00:27:39.110 --> 00:27:40.810
living another 100 years
would be no problem.

00:27:40.810 --> 00:27:41.750
I need to stay by your side.

00:27:41.750 --> 00:27:43.750
I should take better care of myself.

00:27:44.910 --> 00:27:46.260
Shut up.

00:27:46.960 --> 00:27:48.160
Living another 100 years?

00:27:48.160 --> 00:27:49.560
Isn't that frightening?

00:27:51.230 --> 00:27:52.240
What do we have for lunch?

00:27:52.240 --> 00:27:55.000
For lunch? Your favorite stewed beans

00:27:55.310 --> 00:27:56.110
and potatoes.

00:27:56.350 --> 00:27:57.550
Did you buy potatoes?

00:27:59.950 --> 00:28:01.410
I'll go wash the potatoes.

00:28:02.020 --> 00:28:04.000
I'll wash them, peel them,
and cut them up.

00:28:04.000 --> 00:28:04.390
Okay.

00:28:04.640 --> 00:28:06.790
Then wash
the vegetables thoroughly for me.

00:28:06.790 --> 00:28:08.000
I'll get everything ready, and you can
stew them when you come back.

00:28:08.000 --> 00:28:08.440
Okay.

00:28:08.440 --> 00:28:09.240
I'll go in a bit.

00:28:09.240 --> 00:28:09.770
Alright.

00:28:12.230 --> 00:28:13.180
Great.

00:28:13.800 --> 00:28:15.750
He finally came to terms with it.

00:28:17.590 --> 00:28:19.510
I need to go cook.

00:28:21.440 --> 00:28:22.070
Alright.

00:28:22.840 --> 00:28:24.100
Now I can rest assured.

00:28:25.720 --> 00:28:29.050
♪ The liberation zone ♪

00:28:29.410 --> 00:28:32.980
♪ The mass production ♪

00:28:33.010 --> 00:28:33.770
♪ The convoy and the people ♪

00:28:33.770 --> 00:28:34.900
So many people here?

00:28:35.680 --> 00:28:36.150
Are they going to sing

00:28:36.150 --> 00:28:36.590
♪ Chalalalala ♪

00:28:36.590 --> 00:28:38.730
Military-Civilian Mass Production
today too?

00:28:38.730 --> 00:28:41.980
♪ Let's all go ♪

00:28:42.450 --> 00:28:45.700
♪ We clear the forest tops ♪

00:28:46.050 --> 00:28:49.490
♪ We reclaim the wasteland ♪

00:28:49.700 --> 00:28:52.530
♪ There's no difference
between men and women ♪

00:28:52.560 --> 00:28:55.270
♪ Chalalalalalalala ♪

00:28:55.300 --> 00:28:56.550
♪ Come on ♪

00:28:56.550 --> 00:28:58.680
I've learned it by heart
after all these years.

00:28:58.680 --> 00:28:59.280
It's over.

00:28:59.590 --> 00:29:01.270
According to the usual procedure,

00:29:01.270 --> 00:29:02.460
is it supposed to be

00:29:02.480 --> 00:29:05.520
that old man reciting poetry next?

00:29:05.550 --> 00:29:07.750
Yeah, yeah, yeah. We have it every year.

00:29:08.830 --> 00:29:10.030
East Chemical Plant!

00:29:10.790 --> 00:29:12.830
I'm proud of you!

00:29:13.030 --> 00:29:13.550
Why did the performer change?

00:29:13.550 --> 00:29:16.640
-I feel honored because of you!
-The young generation has taken over.

00:29:16.640 --> 00:29:18.700
We are the backbone and marrow

00:29:18.700 --> 00:29:20.760
-of the Republic.
-Do you think

00:29:20.790 --> 00:29:22.510
our program will work?

00:29:22.830 --> 00:29:24.990
Of course!
These are all the same old routine.

00:29:24.990 --> 00:29:26.600
The glory!

00:29:30.120 --> 00:29:31.450
Come on, Xu.

00:29:31.680 --> 00:29:34.750
I've seen these performances
over 1,000 times.

00:29:35.070 --> 00:29:37.510
What's going on?
Don't we have any fresh talent?

00:29:37.510 --> 00:29:38.120
Yes, we do.

00:29:38.170 --> 00:29:40.310
This year there's a guitar performance.

00:29:40.310 --> 00:29:40.590
Right.

00:29:40.590 --> 00:29:41.850
A guitar performance?

00:29:42.200 --> 00:29:43.440
By young people?

00:29:43.460 --> 00:29:44.330
Yes, by young people.

00:29:44.330 --> 00:29:45.510
What song will they sing?

00:29:45.510 --> 00:29:47.480
We Workers Have The Power.

00:29:48.330 --> 00:29:49.680
That sounds interesting.

00:29:49.680 --> 00:29:51.060
-Let them come up then.
-Okay.

00:29:51.060 --> 00:29:52.820
The guitar performance!

00:29:55.240 --> 00:29:56.640
The guitar performance!

00:29:57.000 --> 00:29:57.920
Here!

00:30:06.640 --> 00:30:08.100
I'll make it grand for you.

00:30:14.530 --> 00:30:15.730
They also have a drum.

00:30:19.590 --> 00:30:22.110
Plant leaders, hello.

00:30:25.000 --> 00:30:26.200
My name is Zhuang Sen.

00:30:28.310 --> 00:30:30.550
His name is Zhang Xiaoman.

00:30:33.400 --> 00:30:35.590
We're from the affiliated middle school.

00:30:35.590 --> 00:30:37.590
We also share a common identity—

00:30:38.350 --> 00:30:40.510
children of the East Chemical Plant.

00:30:42.200 --> 00:30:44.450
[Audition for the 30th Anniversary
Celebration of the East Chemical Plant]

00:30:44.880 --> 00:30:47.430
We grew up listening
to our grandfathers' stories about

00:30:47.430 --> 00:30:50.830
digging the first shovelful of black soil
to build the plant.

00:30:51.950 --> 00:30:52.790
He talks too much.

00:30:52.790 --> 00:30:54.310
-Quite a chatterbox.
-Our love for the East Chemical Plant

00:30:54.310 --> 00:30:56.480
is deeply rooted in our hearts.

00:30:57.030 --> 00:30:58.880
In the future, we will certainly

00:30:58.880 --> 00:31:00.510
take over the baton from our fathers

00:31:00.510 --> 00:31:03.510
and become honorable workers.

00:31:07.000 --> 00:31:09.260
So the performance we prepared for today

00:31:10.070 --> 00:31:11.400
is a guitar performance

00:31:11.550 --> 00:31:13.830
of We Workers Have The Power.

00:31:13.920 --> 00:31:14.830
Music!

00:31:15.830 --> 00:31:19.270
♪ We workers have the power ♪

00:31:19.790 --> 00:31:21.790
♪ We workers have the power ♪

00:31:21.880 --> 00:31:25.440
♪ Busy at work every day ♪

00:31:26.000 --> 00:31:27.790
♪ Busy at work every day ♪

00:31:28.000 --> 00:31:30.000
♪ We built towering buildings ♪

00:31:30.000 --> 00:31:32.110
♪ We laid railways and mines ♪

00:31:32.110 --> 00:31:35.880
♪ We changed the world ♪

00:31:36.240 --> 00:31:38.110
♪ For what? For liberation ♪

00:31:38.270 --> 00:31:40.680
♪ For what? For liberation ♪

00:31:43.310 --> 00:31:47.480
♪ It's to free all China ♪

00:31:47.480 --> 00:31:48.070
Bravo!

00:31:58.380 --> 00:32:00.250
Grandma, I have good news for you.

00:32:00.960 --> 00:32:02.020
You found money on the ground?

00:32:02.020 --> 00:32:05.110
No. I was selected
for our anniversary celebration.

00:32:07.840 --> 00:32:09.640
The anniversary celebration.?

00:32:10.110 --> 00:32:12.500
Anyone can participate.

00:32:12.990 --> 00:32:15.030
Look at those old ladies in Building 3.

00:32:15.030 --> 00:32:16.690
They never miss it every year.

00:32:17.110 --> 00:32:20.040
It's different.
This year is completely different.

00:32:20.080 --> 00:32:21.380
Everyone was selected by the union.

00:32:21.380 --> 00:32:22.510
It's very official.

00:32:22.580 --> 00:32:24.680
Zhuang Sen and I were selected together.

00:32:24.680 --> 00:32:27.280
Let's go watch it
on the day of the performance.

00:32:28.350 --> 00:32:29.150
I'm not going.

00:32:29.510 --> 00:32:30.160
Why not?

00:32:30.460 --> 00:32:32.720
Every year the seats they give

00:32:32.750 --> 00:32:34.280
to the elderly and disabled

00:32:34.680 --> 00:32:36.000
are all in the corners.

00:32:36.480 --> 00:32:38.270
I can't see anything even if I go.

00:32:38.270 --> 00:32:38.880
Well...

00:32:41.480 --> 00:32:43.640
It's okay, Grandma.
The program has been selected,

00:32:43.640 --> 00:32:45.390
so I'll definitely get you a good seat.

00:32:45.390 --> 00:32:47.180
Go watch it. I'm leaving now.

00:32:47.840 --> 00:32:48.470
Okay.

00:32:56.160 --> 00:32:56.830
Come in.

00:32:58.640 --> 00:32:59.440
Director Liu.

00:33:00.270 --> 00:33:01.130
Zhang Xiaoman?

00:33:02.220 --> 00:33:03.550
Your program was quite good.

00:33:03.550 --> 00:33:04.570
Quite innovative.

00:33:04.570 --> 00:33:05.920
Thank you, Director Liu.

00:33:05.920 --> 00:33:07.580
Do you need something from me?

00:33:07.890 --> 00:33:08.550
Have a seat.

00:33:10.990 --> 00:33:13.850
I'm performing
in this year's celebration, right?

00:33:14.350 --> 00:33:16.350
I want to get a ticket for my grandma.

00:33:17.400 --> 00:33:19.030
I thought it was something serious.

00:33:19.030 --> 00:33:19.770
You're a performer.

00:33:19.770 --> 00:33:21.510
Of course we'll arrange tickets
for your family and friends.

00:33:21.510 --> 00:33:23.240
Not to mention just one ticket.

00:33:23.580 --> 00:33:25.110
Even if you want 3 or 5 tickets,

00:33:25.110 --> 00:33:26.970
that wouldn't be a problem at all.

00:33:27.310 --> 00:33:28.480
Here, they're all here.

00:33:28.480 --> 00:33:29.810
-Help yourself.
-Okay.

00:33:30.910 --> 00:33:32.640
So many tickets left this year?

00:33:36.200 --> 00:33:37.000
Director Liu.

00:33:37.510 --> 00:33:41.650
My grandma is quite old.

00:33:41.750 --> 00:33:44.400
Her eyes and ears aren't so good.

00:33:44.550 --> 00:33:46.410
Are there any front-row tickets?

00:33:47.030 --> 00:33:48.000
When you're old,

00:33:48.030 --> 00:33:50.820
sitting in the back actually gives you
a better view.

00:33:50.820 --> 00:33:51.540
Besides,

00:33:51.880 --> 00:33:52.960
our plant's

00:33:53.270 --> 00:33:55.780
Workers' Cultural Center
has surround sound.

00:33:55.780 --> 00:33:57.510
Do you know what surround sound is?

00:33:57.510 --> 00:33:59.640
No matter where you sit,

00:33:59.750 --> 00:34:01.030
it feels like the sound

00:34:01.030 --> 00:34:02.720
is swirling

00:34:02.720 --> 00:34:03.580
all around you.

00:34:03.660 --> 00:34:04.920
Every seat is the same.

00:34:05.270 --> 00:34:07.160
If every seat is the same,

00:34:07.640 --> 00:34:09.699
then just give me a front-row ticket.

00:34:11.199 --> 00:34:13.320
Front-row seats are limited.

00:34:13.340 --> 00:34:15.070
We have plant leaders and their families,

00:34:15.070 --> 00:34:16.739
branch plant leaders and their families,

00:34:16.739 --> 00:34:18.100
labor models,

00:34:18.130 --> 00:34:19.630
March 8th Red Flag Bearers,

00:34:19.630 --> 00:34:22.550
and those who made contributions
in the early days of the plant.

00:34:22.550 --> 00:34:24.080
There aren't enough seats.

00:34:24.870 --> 00:34:25.800
Contributions?

00:34:26.840 --> 00:34:28.500
My grandpa was a contributor.

00:34:28.850 --> 00:34:29.780
He was a war hero.

00:34:30.110 --> 00:34:31.070
Your grandpa?

00:34:31.590 --> 00:34:32.590
What was his name?

00:34:32.590 --> 00:34:33.520
Zhang Hansheng.

00:34:34.030 --> 00:34:35.030
My grandma told me

00:34:35.320 --> 00:34:37.280
that my grandpa participated in

00:34:37.800 --> 00:34:39.190
the Pingjin Campaign,

00:34:39.280 --> 00:34:40.150
the Liaoshen Campaign,

00:34:40.150 --> 00:34:41.230
and the Crossing of the Yangtze.

00:34:41.230 --> 00:34:42.800
He was undoubtedly a contributor,
wasn't he?

00:34:42.800 --> 00:34:45.110
Zhang Hansheng. I know him.

00:34:46.230 --> 00:34:48.960
Well... your grandpa was indeed a veteran.

00:34:49.440 --> 00:34:50.000
But...

00:34:50.000 --> 00:34:53.550
it seems he never received any citations.

00:34:54.250 --> 00:34:56.480
Have you ever seen

00:34:56.510 --> 00:34:57.730
anything he left behind,

00:34:57.730 --> 00:34:59.600
like certificates or medals?

00:35:05.030 --> 00:35:05.760
You're back?

00:35:12.990 --> 00:35:13.650
Let me do it.

00:35:13.650 --> 00:35:14.510
I'll handle it.

00:35:18.260 --> 00:35:19.480
Where's the beginning part?

00:35:19.480 --> 00:35:20.030
It's here.

00:35:20.030 --> 00:35:20.550
Here.

00:35:21.910 --> 00:35:22.740
Alright.

00:35:23.030 --> 00:35:23.630
Done?

00:35:29.030 --> 00:35:29.630
Grandma.

00:35:30.550 --> 00:35:32.610
My grandpa fought in so many battles.

00:35:32.800 --> 00:35:34.630
Don't we have anything

00:35:34.630 --> 00:35:36.590
like medals or certificates?

00:35:37.000 --> 00:35:37.920
Medals?

00:35:39.230 --> 00:35:40.920
I think I saw one before.

00:35:40.920 --> 00:35:42.180
Where is it? Let me see.

00:35:42.510 --> 00:35:43.590
I've long forgotten.

00:35:43.590 --> 00:35:45.150
I don't know where I put it.

00:35:45.800 --> 00:35:47.220
It's nothing special anyway.

00:35:47.220 --> 00:35:48.480
Every soldier got one.

00:35:49.150 --> 00:35:50.630
So was my grandpa...

00:35:51.670 --> 00:35:52.840
a hero?

00:35:53.550 --> 00:35:55.410
Of course your grandpa was a hero.

00:35:55.590 --> 00:35:57.590
Even if he was just a common soldier,

00:35:57.710 --> 00:35:58.670
he risked his life

00:35:58.670 --> 00:36:00.400
fighting battle after battle.

00:36:00.800 --> 00:36:03.190
Besides, your grandpa didn't join the army

00:36:03.190 --> 00:36:06.120
to earn some medal.

00:36:09.550 --> 00:36:10.030
Here.

00:36:10.060 --> 00:36:10.620
Yes.

00:36:11.960 --> 00:36:13.160
My grandpa was a hero.

00:36:16.760 --> 00:36:17.290
Grandma.

00:36:17.800 --> 00:36:19.030
What do you think if I

00:36:19.360 --> 00:36:21.220
join the army like my grandpa did?

00:36:21.300 --> 00:36:22.960
Of course that would be great.

00:36:23.190 --> 00:36:24.510
Look at your height.

00:36:24.880 --> 00:36:26.140
In a military uniform,

00:36:26.890 --> 00:36:30.210
you'd look just as handsome
as your grandpa.

00:36:31.880 --> 00:36:32.670
Really?

00:36:33.800 --> 00:36:35.150
People always say

00:36:35.440 --> 00:36:38.360
that genes skip a generation.

00:36:38.360 --> 00:36:39.550
It's quite weird.

00:36:39.960 --> 00:36:43.460
Look at your profile and head shape.

00:36:44.190 --> 00:36:46.450
They look just like your grandfather's.

00:36:48.510 --> 00:36:50.370
The first time I saw your grandpa,

00:36:50.760 --> 00:36:52.890
he was wearing a military uniform too.

00:36:53.000 --> 00:36:54.840
Among so many people,

00:36:55.190 --> 00:36:56.520
he was the only one I saw.

00:36:58.000 --> 00:36:59.840
Grandma, you've never told me

00:36:59.840 --> 00:37:02.150
the love story between you and Grandpa.

00:37:02.200 --> 00:37:03.220
Tell me about it.

00:37:04.550 --> 00:37:06.190
You young people...

00:37:06.330 --> 00:37:08.150
Always talking about love.

00:37:09.580 --> 00:37:13.060
Your grandfather and I just clicked.

00:37:39.190 --> 00:37:40.000
Director Liu.

00:37:41.920 --> 00:37:43.450
Why is it you again?

00:37:43.920 --> 00:37:46.520
If you're still asking
for front-row tickets,

00:37:46.960 --> 00:37:48.290
I really can't help you.

00:37:49.670 --> 00:37:50.470
Director Liu.

00:37:54.440 --> 00:37:55.880
As Xiaoman's partner,

00:37:56.360 --> 00:37:57.150
I think

00:37:57.610 --> 00:38:00.450
you could consider
giving him a front-row ticket

00:38:00.510 --> 00:38:01.710
to satisfy his needs.

00:38:02.280 --> 00:38:04.070
Front-row tickets are limited.

00:38:04.070 --> 00:38:05.150
You can't expect me

00:38:05.150 --> 00:38:06.880
to conjure up a front-row seat.

00:38:09.190 --> 00:38:10.590
Well, if that's the case,

00:38:10.880 --> 00:38:14.410
we're withdrawing from this year's
anniversary celebration.

00:38:16.070 --> 00:38:17.880
As for this anniversary celebration,

00:38:17.880 --> 00:38:18.960
because of your mistake,

00:38:18.960 --> 00:38:20.760
you lost the biggest highlight.

00:38:20.810 --> 00:38:22.850
I think you need to think about that.

00:38:37.750 --> 00:38:39.610
I didn't expect Liu to be so tough.

00:38:39.960 --> 00:38:43.020
He actually removed our performance
from the program.

00:38:48.590 --> 00:38:49.440
Zhuang Cent.

00:38:50.610 --> 00:38:51.500
This time...

00:38:52.490 --> 00:38:53.490
I'm really sorry.

00:38:55.080 --> 00:38:56.810
Just for getting me a ticket...

00:38:57.780 --> 00:38:58.490
It's fine.

00:38:59.360 --> 00:39:00.280
I, Zhuang C—

00:39:00.960 --> 00:39:01.880
Zhuang Sen,

00:39:03.240 --> 00:39:04.040
never give up.

00:39:06.810 --> 00:39:07.210
Right.

00:39:08.030 --> 00:39:08.840
Didn't you say

00:39:08.840 --> 00:39:10.510
he still has quite a few tickets
that haven't been distributed?

00:39:10.510 --> 00:39:13.110
There are plenty left.
They're all over there.

00:39:14.560 --> 00:39:15.760
Then I know what to do.

00:39:15.960 --> 00:39:16.890
What do you mean?

00:39:17.920 --> 00:39:18.710
Just watch.

00:39:21.800 --> 00:39:22.600
Director Liu!

00:39:23.710 --> 00:39:24.510
Director Liu!

00:39:24.760 --> 00:39:25.550
What are you doing?

00:39:25.550 --> 00:39:26.280
I'm sorry.

00:39:27.330 --> 00:39:28.860
I got carried away just now.

00:39:29.820 --> 00:39:31.130
Please be magnanimous

00:39:31.550 --> 00:39:32.470
and forgive us this once.

00:39:32.470 --> 00:39:33.360
Yes, Director Liu.

00:39:33.360 --> 00:39:34.890
We promise to perform well.

00:39:36.280 --> 00:39:38.710
-We'll definitely do our best
-We will do our best.

00:39:38.710 --> 00:39:40.910
for the anniversary celebration. Yes.

00:39:41.030 --> 00:39:43.550
Your attitude is quite good.

00:39:44.760 --> 00:39:45.710
Young people,

00:39:46.150 --> 00:39:48.710
don't keep challenging the plant

00:39:49.800 --> 00:39:51.430
and the leadership, okay?

00:39:51.760 --> 00:39:52.710
-Yes.
-Yes, sir.

00:39:52.840 --> 00:39:55.400
About this anniversary celebration,

00:39:55.670 --> 00:39:56.840
it won't make much difference
if you're in it

00:39:56.840 --> 00:39:57.840
or if you're not.

00:39:57.860 --> 00:39:58.500
Yes.

00:39:58.520 --> 00:39:59.320
Absolutely right.

00:39:59.320 --> 00:40:00.900
Don't think too highly of yourself.

00:40:00.900 --> 00:40:01.650
Yes.

00:40:02.070 --> 00:40:04.070
So you agreed to let us perform?

00:40:08.280 --> 00:40:10.550
Considering your good attitude.

00:40:11.070 --> 00:40:12.110
But don't let this happen again.

00:40:12.110 --> 00:40:13.280
Thank you, Director Liu.

00:40:13.280 --> 00:40:14.230
-Sure.
-Thank you, Director Liu.

00:40:14.230 --> 00:40:14.830
Director.

00:40:15.910 --> 00:40:17.710
About that front-row ticket...

00:40:18.110 --> 00:40:19.590
Will you ever stop?

00:40:19.760 --> 00:40:20.550
There are no tickets.

00:40:20.550 --> 00:40:21.340
Perform or don't.

00:40:21.340 --> 00:40:22.150
Director Liu.

00:40:23.070 --> 00:40:25.630
I heard that many tickets
weren't given out.

00:40:26.510 --> 00:40:28.230
Who said that? Who told you?

00:40:28.230 --> 00:40:29.150
No one. I didn't hear it from anyone.

00:40:29.150 --> 00:40:30.590
I specifically reserved those

00:40:30.590 --> 00:40:32.510
for the staff's

00:40:32.510 --> 00:40:33.760
friends and family.

00:40:33.880 --> 00:40:34.880
I understand.

00:40:35.480 --> 00:40:36.880
If you need,

00:40:37.470 --> 00:40:39.930
I can help you
distribute all these tickets.

00:40:40.950 --> 00:40:41.980
Really?

00:40:42.000 --> 00:40:42.930
Would I lie?

00:40:43.110 --> 00:40:43.800
Absolutely!

00:40:43.800 --> 00:40:45.530
He can do it. He can handle this.

00:40:46.150 --> 00:40:48.300
I guarantee the anniversary celebration
will be packed

00:40:48.300 --> 00:40:49.420
and lively.

00:40:50.670 --> 00:40:53.480
So who do you plan
to give these tickets to?

00:40:53.710 --> 00:40:55.440
You don't trust me, Zuang Cent—

00:40:58.040 --> 00:40:59.370
He always calls me that.

00:40:59.440 --> 00:41:00.840
Zhuang Sen's influence.

00:41:02.780 --> 00:41:03.700
My classmates—

00:41:03.730 --> 00:41:06.040
if they know Xiaoman and I will perform

00:41:06.320 --> 00:41:08.920
on such a big stage at our plant,

00:41:09.280 --> 00:41:10.620
they'll be jumping to come!

00:41:10.620 --> 00:41:11.620
They'll all come.

00:41:11.950 --> 00:41:12.540
Right.

00:41:14.360 --> 00:41:14.890
Alright.

00:41:20.920 --> 00:41:22.110
Second row, center.

00:41:22.230 --> 00:41:23.840
I really don't have better tickets.

00:41:23.840 --> 00:41:25.550
I knew you had extra tickets!

00:41:25.840 --> 00:41:26.960
Extra my foot.

00:41:26.960 --> 00:41:28.360
This is my wife's ticket.

00:41:29.430 --> 00:41:30.630
That's not appropriate.

00:41:30.630 --> 00:41:32.490
How will you explain this at home?

00:41:33.280 --> 00:41:34.610
I can make this decision.

00:41:34.610 --> 00:41:36.920
We need to prioritize the bigger picture.

00:41:36.920 --> 00:41:37.550
Thank you so much.

00:41:37.550 --> 00:41:40.440
Besides, my wife
understands the bigger picture too.

00:41:40.440 --> 00:41:43.300
Here are the tickets.
Come get more if you need them.

00:41:44.030 --> 00:41:46.480
But you two must guarantee that...

00:41:46.480 --> 00:41:47.340
I guarantee it.

00:41:47.390 --> 00:41:49.210
I, Zhuang Sen,
guarantee to complete the mission.

00:41:49.210 --> 00:41:51.340
If I fail, I'll quit the stage forever.

00:41:51.590 --> 00:41:52.920
I'll go to our plant gate

00:41:52.920 --> 00:41:53.780
and read a self-criticism.

00:41:53.780 --> 00:41:54.280
Right?

00:41:54.280 --> 00:41:55.610
Stop talking nonsense.

00:41:56.280 --> 00:41:56.840
Xiaoman,

00:41:57.230 --> 00:41:58.030
do your best.

00:41:58.030 --> 00:41:59.230
Perform well for your grandma.

00:41:59.230 --> 00:41:59.960
Don't worry.

00:42:00.630 --> 00:42:01.030
Go on.

00:42:01.860 --> 00:42:02.550
Thank you, Director Liu.

00:42:02.550 --> 00:42:03.950
Thank you, Director Liu.

00:42:05.480 --> 00:42:06.760
The middle seat ticket?

00:42:06.760 --> 00:42:07.510
Got it, huh?

00:42:08.400 --> 00:42:10.260
Stop calling me Sun Cent anymore.

00:42:10.510 --> 00:42:11.230
Zhuang Sen,

00:42:12.550 --> 00:42:13.800
you're really good at acting humble.

00:42:13.800 --> 00:42:14.460
Seriously.

00:42:15.030 --> 00:42:15.670
Shut up.

00:42:16.440 --> 00:42:17.070
Grandma!

00:42:17.840 --> 00:42:18.370
Grandma!

00:42:19.650 --> 00:42:20.790
I got the ticket. See?

00:42:20.790 --> 00:42:21.550
I got the ticket.

00:42:21.550 --> 00:42:22.840
What are you being cocky about this time?

00:42:22.840 --> 00:42:23.630
Come inside.

00:42:25.710 --> 00:42:27.670
Grandma, I got it.

00:42:28.630 --> 00:42:30.030
Second row, middle seat.

00:42:31.240 --> 00:42:32.520
You can see everything from there.

00:42:32.520 --> 00:42:33.670
Exactly.

00:42:34.820 --> 00:42:36.340
My grandson is so capable.

00:42:36.480 --> 00:42:38.800
Well, I always make sure
everything's perfect for my grandma.

00:42:38.800 --> 00:42:39.770
Alright, I'm going now.

00:42:39.770 --> 00:42:41.070
Wait, don't go yet. Come here.

00:42:41.070 --> 00:42:43.430
Let me take your measurements. Come on.

00:42:43.510 --> 00:42:44.550
What's this? For my waist?

00:42:44.550 --> 00:42:45.430
Yes.

00:42:45.710 --> 00:42:46.550
It's too big.

00:42:47.320 --> 00:42:48.540
It's too big this year,

00:42:48.540 --> 00:42:50.670
but it'll fit perfectly in a year or two.

00:42:50.670 --> 00:42:52.190
Fine. You keep knitting. I'm leaving.